    "patch_code": "private static ZipLong unixTimeToZipLong(long l) {\n    final long TWO_TO_32 = 0x100000000L;\n    // Change <= to < as we don't want to handle the case where the timestamp is exactly equal to 2^32 - 1\n    if (l >= TWO_TO_32) {\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"X5455 timestamps must fit in a signed 32 bit integer: \" + l);\n    }\n    return new ZipLong(l);\n}",
